						the Superintendent receives a formal complaint against the nonpublic school. In the latter two cases, the Superintendent shall conduct an onsite review at least annually.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) In carrying out this subdivision, the Superintendent shall verify that the nonpublic school has received a successful criminal background check clearance and has enrolled in subsequent arrest notice service pursuant to Section 44237 for each owner, operator, and employee of the nonpublic school, and pursuant to Section 33192 for each contractor of the nonpublic school.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) Commencing with the 2026–27 school year, the Superintendent shall also do all of the following before certifying a nonpublic school located outside of California:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) Review assurances provided pursuant to paragraph (8) of subdivision (a) relating to behavioral interventions to evaluate consistency with California laws.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) Ensure that pupils have been provided a copy of their rights and procedural safeguards, as referenced in Section 300.504(a) of Title 34 of the Code of Federal Regulations, and information on how to contact the department’s Constituent Services Office, upon admission to the nonpublic school and that this information is accessible and require the telephone number for the department’s Constituent Services Office to be prominently displayed at the nonpublic school.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) Review policies, procedures, and practices of the nonpublic school to determine if there is a clear and confidential process for residents to
